article.headline: Marquette scores season-high 101, beats Oregon in NIT

images.name: Rowsey's lights-out shooting key to Marquette's win over Oregon
images.caption: Mitch Holthus and Jason Capel break down the electric performance from Andrew Rowsey in Marquette's 101-92 win over Oregon.

article.linkText: Marquette scores season-high 101, beats Oregon in NIT
article.story: MILWAUKEE -- Andrew Rowsey scored 29 points and dished out nine assists and Marquette had its highest-scoring output of the season in a 101-92 victory over Oregon on Sunday to advance to the quarterfinals of the NIT. Rowsey scored 16 of Marquette's 30 first-quarter points as the Golden Eagles led by 11 points. He was 5 of 6 from distance, including a 4-point play for a 21-11 lead. Marquette scored a season-high 58 points before halftime for the most points allowed in a half by Oregon this season. The Golden Eagles shot 57 percent from the field in the first 20 minutes, including 10 of 19 from distance. Marquette led by 25 points early in the fourth quarter and kept a double-digit lead until Payton Pritchard's dunk at the final horn. Markus Howard made four 3-pointers and scored 18 points for Marquette (21-13), which plays Penn State on Tuesday. Rowsey finished with six 3-pointers -- for the sixth time this season. MiKyle McIntosh went 15 of 18 from the free-throw line -- both career highs -- and scored 25 points for Oregon (23-13). Paul White scored a career-high 19 points and Pritchard scored seven of Oregon's first nine points but went scoreless the rest of the quarter and finished with 16. ---- More AP college basketball: https://collegebasketball.ap.org; https://twitter.com/AP-Top25 and https://www.podcastone.com/ap-sports-special-events

videos.headline: Marquette's ball movement leads to John's slam
videos.description: Sam Hauser leads Theo John to the rim for an emphatic two-handed slam.

videos.headline: Froling's steal sets up Rowsey's transition 3
videos.description: Following a steal from Harry Froling, Andrew Rowsey finds an opening behind the arc and nails a transition 3-pointer.

videos.headline: Rowsey converts 4-point play for Golden Eagles
videos.description: Andrew Rowsey finds space off a screen and sinks a contested 3-pointer to earn the chance at a 4-point play.

videos.headline: Roswey spins to convert 5th 3-pointer of quarter
videos.description: Andrew Rowsey loses his defender on a spin move and nails another 3-point bucket to make him 5-of-6 from downtown in the first quarter.

videos.headline: Heldt finishes layup through contact for and-1 chance
videos.description: Sam Hauser feeds Matt Heldt in the paint for a contested layup through a foul to earn an opportunity for a 3-point play.

videos.headline: Brown's dime sets up Bailey's crafty layup
videos.description: Oregon's Troy Brown whips a behind-the-back pass to Victor Bailey Jr. in transition for a tough Oregon layup.

videos.headline: Cain throws down emphatic alley-oop slam
videos.description: Andrew Rowsey lofts a pass up to Jamal Cain at the rim for a thunderous two-handed finish.

videos.headline: Elliott fired up after and-1 layup
videos.description: Greg Elliott takes it to the paint and finishes the transition lay-in for an opportunity at a 3-point play.

videos.headline: Wooten turns defense into instant offense
videos.description: After grabbing a steal off the inbounds, Kenny Wooten flushes a one-handed slam for the Ducks.

videos.headline: Rowsey connects with John on alley-oop finish
videos.description: While falling over, Andrew Rowsey lobs a pass up to Theo John at the rim for a two-handed slam in the third quarter.
